HEADWORD: Megalops
<hw>Meg"a*lops</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧g"⟦adot⟧*l⟦ocr⟧ps)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>me`gas</grk>, <grk>-a`loy</grk>, large +
<grk>'w`ps</grk> eye.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
larva, in a stage following the zoea, in the development of most crabs.
In this stage the legs and abdominal appendages have appeared, the
abdomen is relatively long, and the eyes are large. Also used
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A large fish; the tarpum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>megalopsychy</ent>⟦br⟧
